snippet: At least six people were killed, including a Navy SEAL member, in the rescue of Dr. Dilip Joseph, who was abducted Wednesday.
abstract: Officials say American doctor Dilip Joseph was rescued from Taliban capture by Afghan and coalitions forces in eastern Afghanistan; say at least six people were killed during operation, including an American, and two Taliban leaders were arrested during raid.

byline.original: By SHARIFULLAH SAHAK and AZAM AHMED

lead_paragraph: At least six people were killed, including a Navy SEAL member, in the rescue of Dr. Dilip Joseph, who was abducted Wednesday.

headline.seo: American Doctor, Dilip Joseph, Rescued in Afghanistan
headline.main: Afghan and Coalition Forces Rescue American Doctor Who Was Kidnapped by Taliban
